y their country, whether loyalty to one’s friends is more important than patriotism and whether we can really trust the intelligence services.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aFilm and Media Studies 2021. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  a1980s counter-culture.  aAlan Turing.  aCambridge spies.  aCold War.  aGay Rights.  aOfficial Secrets Act.  aPatriotism.  aProfumo Affair.  aThatcherism.  aclass privilege.1 aBolton, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packagez978311128198840uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614847640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526148476423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526148476/original  a978-3-11-128198-8  Manchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packageb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles